SUMMARY:VGM CON Panels Overview
LOCATION:Panels 1/Conference Room E
DESCRIPTION:Want to know what's going on in Panel Rooms 1 and 2 over the w
 eekend? This panel is about just that. Dr. James HD\, the panel's coordina
 tor\, will provide an overview of the many awesome panels happening at thi
 s year's VGM CON 🤓 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:daaf898c464467497b0290cb005d40f6
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20250328T000000Z
DTSTART:20250411T140000
DTEND:20250411T145500
SUMMARY:Composing with Global Music Traditions for Video Games
LOCATION:Panels 2/Conference Room D
DESCRIPTION:Video games allow players to explore virtual worlds\, sometime
 s fantastical and other times reminiscent of our own\, real world. The vis
 uals and audio of these virtual worlds establish a sense of place and time
 \, based on the players’ conceptions of cultural and historical signifie
 rs. Intended for composers and music nerds\, this panel led by composer Jo
 hn MacDonald will explore difficulties encountered when composing video ga
 me music that draws from real-world musical traditions\, including preserv
 ation (or lack thereof) of musical traditions\, problematic musical misrep
 resentation\, research methods of non-Western music for Western-trained mu
 sicians\, and defying or reinforcing culture-specific tropes. 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:a82d27f04473fc10cf690a3b26294a43
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20250328T000000Z
DTSTART:20250411T144500
DTEND:20250411T154000
SUMMARY:Watch Karl Create a Sega Genesis Song in 55 min!
LOCATION:Panels 1/Conference Room E
DESCRIPTION:Join composer Karl Brueggemann as he battles against the clock
  to create a (good) Sega Genesis tune in just 55 minutes! To add more pres
 sure\, Karl commits that whatever he creates on this panel stage\, he will
  include on his upcoming FM Synth album High Flyer 2! Gotta compose fast! 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:e80c9d8b1d84a97004d38164d955e4fa
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20250328T000000Z
DTSTART:20250411T151500
DTEND:20250411T161000
SUMMARY:VGM as a Vehicle for Introductory Jazz Arranging
LOCATION:Panels 2/Conference Room D
DESCRIPTION:Video game music and jazz standards have more in common than o
 ne might initially think! This panel will dive into the shared elements of
  music from those two worlds\, and provide some basic techniques for the n
 ew jazz arranger. 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:007392bccd2200dce0d2ba2d7676d1e7
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20250328T000000Z
DTSTART:20250411T160000
DTEND:20250411T165500
SUMMARY:Video Game Music Education for Everyone
LOCATION:Panels 1/Conference Room E
DESCRIPTION:Let's talk about teaching video game music education! Dr. Nico
 le Harvey (@RedAuxPDX) Associate Professor at the University of Portland\,
  will discuss her approach in teaching game music history and appreciation
  to a mostly STEM-focused student base\, as well as the development of her
  video game music class into the university's core humanities curriculum. 
 Jeremy Tellock (@DucksinDisguise)\, Director of Production and Design at P
 ixel Pond will discuss teaching students to compose music for games utiliz
 ing DAWs and FL Studio. 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:5eb94078bac58f1b8af692347cdcf5c5
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20250328T000000Z
DTSTART:20250411T163000
DTEND:20250411T172500
SUMMARY:Voicings and Textures: Make Your Music Move!
LOCATION:Panels 2/Conference Room D
DESCRIPTION:Not sure how to build a chord? Don't know what rhythms to writ
 e? This panel will focus on one of the most overlooked elements of arrangi
 ng: voicings\, the way we choose to stack a chord and build off of it. Poo
 r voicings can muddy an arrangement without you even knowing\, while great
  ones can make it shine. And from there\, we will see how you can turn tho
 se voicings into textures: moving lines for your musicians to perform. Thi
 s step-by-step process will give you a great idea on how to approach your 
 next arrangement\, and could even forever improve your entire music-making
  process! 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:56687498913c9221637ce5eebe54df52
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20250328T000000Z
DTSTART:20250411T180000
DTEND:20250411T185500
SUMMARY:SCORE! Crafting a Complete Soundtrack
LOCATION:Panels 1/Conference Room E
DESCRIPTION:What makes a great score so moving and memorable? Enjoy an exc
 iting and accessible tour through the building of a would-be-gamescore as 
 we construct musical story from the inside out. Weâ€™ll explore what 
 makes certain melodic choices so powerful\, how to evolve/explode your mat
 erial and how to uniquely support interactive media. Open for absolutely a
 ll\; fans and professionals alike. 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:18c576d732bf2df7e9dd1d23d234e0aa
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20250328T000000Z
DTSTART:20250411T183000
DTEND:20250411T192500
SUMMARY:Inject some life and love into your music videos!
LOCATION:Panels 2/Conference Room D
DESCRIPTION:After several years of improvement\, I've often been told that
  my music videos feel full of love\, alive\, and engaging. I'm not a profe
 ssional videographer\, so in that light\, this is a presentation of the pr
 actical strategies and methods I've used to get my videos to this point. T
 hese will level up the look and feel of your performances\, and properly c
 onvey the care which goes into making your videos. Examples will include r
 udimentary color grading\, angle selection\, simple movement\, gimbal usag
 e\, and lens selection. Nothing here is advanced\, just simple strategies\
 , easy to understand\, and with huge payoff compared to the effort to lear
 n. 
END:VEVENT
