SUMMARY:The Music Theory of Sick Beats
LOCATION:Panels 1/Conference Room E
DESCRIPTION:This is going to be a highly educational panel all about rhyth
 ms\, time signatures\, and the sickest beats imaginable. In both my underg
 rad and master's degrees\, as well as spending lots of time studying Sunga
 zer and Tigran Hamasayan music\, I've developed a fascination for highly r
 hythmic based music. I wanted to distill what I know about rhythms into a 
 short 60 minute presentation. Here we are going to break down rhythmic con
 cepts from beginner to advanced\, picking apart songs across video game hi
 story\, and ultimately answering the question that has plagued humanity si
 nce the dawn of time: What truly is the sickest beat? 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:297654079249240a3e72af723d235401
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20250328T000000Z
DTSTART:20250412T183000
DTEND:20250412T192500
SUMMARY:Pixelated Audio Podcast in Space!
LOCATION:Panels 2/Conference Room D
DESCRIPTION:In honor of this year's VGMCon\, Pixelated Audio is digging in
 to game audio history for some of the best space-themed game music from th
 e serene to the downright baffling. Join us as we listen to some great VGM
  across the decades\, space and time. 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:6c6b8266ddc557ebd099c7f66ab75e6f
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20250328T000000Z
DTSTART:20250412T191500
DTEND:20250412T201000
SUMMARY:Compoverse: How Compos Help Musicians Grow
LOCATION:Panels 1/Conference Room E
DESCRIPTION:During this panel\, Doug Arley (sgtrama) and starla will discu
 ss Compoverse\, a platform by ThaSauce Network for hosting and participati
 ng in community composition competitions\, AKA "compos." Panelists will ex
 plore a brief history of compos and explain how compos aid beginner and ex
 perienced musicians by creating a safe space for experimentation\, offerin
 g opportunities to develop crucial workflows\, and providing them with imm
 ediate feedback\, all under strict restraints. 
END:VEVENT
